# entities

Extract named entities from text using specification-based extraction. Supports custom entity types with flexible extraction rules.

## Usage

```javascript
import entities from './index.js';

// Create an extractor (generates a new specification on each call to the returned function)
const extractCompanies = entities('Extract all company names mentioned');
const result = await extractCompanies('Apple and Microsoft announced a partnership with Google.');
// { entities: [{ name: 'Apple', type: 'company' }, ...] }
```

**Performance note:** The default export generates a new specification on every call to the returned function. For batch processing, use `createEntityExtractor` with a pre-generated specification instead (see Advanced Usage).

## API

### Default Export: `entities(prompt, config)`

Returns a function that extracts entities from text. Each call to the returned function generates a fresh specification — convenient for one-off use, expensive for repeated calls.

The returned function has a `.prompt` property for introspection.

### `extractEntities(text, instructions, config)`

Extract entities from a single text. Generates a specification and applies it in one call.

### `entitySpec(prompt, config)`

Generate a reusable entity extraction specification.

### `applyEntities(text, specification, config)`

Apply a pre-generated specification to extract entities from text. Returns `{ entities: [{ name, type }, ...] }`.

### `createEntityExtractor(specification, config)`

Create a reusable extractor function from a pre-generated specification. The returned function has a `.specification` property.

See [shared configuration](../README.md#shared-configuration) for `llm`, `maxAttempts`, `onProgress`, and `now`.

## Advanced Usage

### Pre-generated Specifications

For consistent, efficient extraction across multiple documents:

```javascript
import { entitySpec, createEntityExtractor } from './index.js';

// Generate specification once (1 LLM call)
const spec = await entitySpec('Extract medical entities: symptoms, diagnoses, medications');

// Create reusable extractor (0 LLM calls)
const medicalExtractor = createEntityExtractor(spec);

// Each extraction uses only 1 LLM call (not 2)
const record1 = await medicalExtractor('Patient reports headache. Prescribed ibuprofen.');
const record2 = await medicalExtractor('MRI scan normal. Diagnosed with migraine.');
```

### Collection Instruction Builders

Create instructions for use with collection chains. All require a pre-generated `specification`:

```javascript
import { entitySpec, mapInstructions, reduceInstructions } from './index.js';
import map from '../map/index.js';
import reduce from '../reduce/index.js';

const spec = await entitySpec('Extract people and companies');

// Extract from each document
const entitySets = await map(documents, mapInstructions({ specification: spec }));

// Consolidate across documents
const allEntities = await reduce(
  entitySets,
  reduceInstructions({
    specification: spec,
    processing: 'Merge duplicates and build comprehensive entity list'
  })
);
```

Available builders — all take `{ specification, processing? }`:

| Builder | Use with | Purpose |
|---------|----------|---------|
| `mapInstructions` | `map` | Extract entities from each item |
| `filterInstructions` | `filter` | Filter items by entity criteria |
| `findInstructions` | `find` | Select item by entity criteria |
| `groupInstructions` | `group` | Group items by entity patterns |
| `reduceInstructions` | `reduce` | Consolidate entities across items |

